39#define TRACE(x) \
40 do { \
41 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_inlining) { \
42 StdoutStream() << x << "\n"; \
43 } \
44 } while (false)

46// Provides convenience accessors for the common layout of nodes having either
47// the {JSCall} or the {JSConstruct} operator.
48class JSCallAccessor {
49 public:
50 explicit JSCallAccessor(Node* call) : call_(call) {
51 DCHECK(call->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall ||
52 call->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct);
53 }
54
55 Node* target() const {
56 return call_->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::TargetIndex());
57 }
58
59 Node* receiver() const { return JSCallNode{call_}.receiver(); }
60
61 Node* new_target() const { return JSConstructNode{call_}.new_target(); }
62
63 FrameState frame_state() const {
64 return FrameState{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(call_)};
65 }
66
67 int argument_count() const {
68 return (call_->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall)
69 ? JSCallNode{call_}.ArgumentCount()
70 : JSConstructNode{call_}.ArgumentCount();
71 }
72
73 CallFrequency const& frequency() const {
74 return (call_->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall)
75 ? JSCallNode{call_}.Parameters().frequency()
76 : JSConstructNode{call_}.Parameters().frequency();
77 }
78
79 private:
80 Node* call_;
81};

85 Node* context, Node* frame_state,
86 StartNode start, Node* end,
87 Node* exception_target,

93 static_cast<int>(n.Parameters().signature()->parameter_count()));
94}

97Reduction JSInliner::InlineCall(Node* call, Node* new_target, Node* context,
98 Node* frame_state, StartNode start, Node* end,
99 Node* exception_target,
100 const NodeVector& uncaught_subcalls,
101 int argument_count) {
102 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IrOpcode::IsInlineeOpcode(call->opcode()),
103 argument_count == JSCallAccessor(call).argument_count());
104
105 // The scheduler is smart enough to place our code; we just ensure {control}
106 // becomes the control input of the start of the inlinee, and {effect} becomes
107 // the effect input of the start of the inlinee.
108 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(call);
109 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(call);
110
111 int const inlinee_new_target_index = start.NewTargetOutputIndex();
112 int const inlinee_arity_index = start.ArgCountOutputIndex();
113 int const inlinee_context_index = start.ContextOutputIndex();
114
115 // {inliner_inputs} counts the target, receiver/new_target, and arguments; but
116 // not feedback vector, context, effect or control.
117 const int inliner_inputs = argument_count +
118 JSCallOrConstructNode::kExtraInputCount -
119 JSCallOrConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorInputCount;
120 // Iterate over all uses of the start node.
121 for (Edge edge : start->use_edges()) {
122 Node* use = edge.from();
123 switch (use->opcode()) {
124 case IrOpcode::kParameter: {
125 int index = 1 + ParameterIndexOf(use->op());
126 DCHECK_LE(index, inlinee_context_index);
127 if (index < inliner_inputs && index < inlinee_new_target_index) {
128 // There is an input from the call, and the index is a value
129 // projection but not the context, so rewire the input.
130 Replace(use, call->InputAt(index));
131 } else if (index == inlinee_new_target_index) {
132 // The projection is requesting the new target value.
133 Replace(use, new_target);
134 } else if (index == inlinee_arity_index) {
135 // The projection is requesting the number of arguments.
136 Replace(use, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(argument_count));
137 } else if (index == inlinee_context_index) {
138 // The projection is requesting the inlinee function context.
139 Replace(use, context);
140 } else {
141 // Call has fewer arguments than required, fill with undefined.
142 Replace(use, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
143 }
144 break;
145 }
146 default:
147 if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
148 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
149 } else if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
150 edge.UpdateTo(control);
151 } else if (NodeProperties::IsFrameStateEdge(edge)) {
152 edge.UpdateTo(frame_state);
153 } else {
154 UNREACHABLE();
155 }
156 break;
157 }
158 }
159
160 if (exception_target != nullptr) {
161 // Link uncaught calls in the inlinee to {exception_target}
162 int subcall_count = static_cast<int>(uncaught_subcalls.size());
163 if (subcall_count > 0) {
164 TRACE("Inlinee contains " << subcall_count
165 << " calls without local exception handler; "
166 << "linking to surrounding exception handler.");
167 }
168 NodeVector on_exception_nodes(local_zone_);
169 for (Node* subcall : uncaught_subcalls) {
170 Node* on_success = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), subcall);
171 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(subcall, subcall, subcall, on_success);
172 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_success, subcall);
173 Node* on_exception =
174 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), subcall, subcall);
175 on_exception_nodes.push_back(on_exception);
176 }
177
178 DCHECK_EQ(subcall_count, static_cast<int>(on_exception_nodes.size()));
179 if (subcall_count > 0) {
180 Node* control_output =
181 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(subcall_count), subcall_count,
182 &on_exception_nodes.front());
183 NodeVector values_effects(local_zone_);
184 values_effects = on_exception_nodes;
185 values_effects.push_back(control_output);
186 Node* value_output = graph()->NewNode(
187 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, subcall_count),
188 subcall_count + 1, &values_effects.front());
189 Node* effect_output =
190 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(subcall_count),
191 subcall_count + 1, &values_effects.front());
192 ReplaceWithValue(exception_target, value_output, effect_output,
193 control_output);
194 } else {
195 ReplaceWithValue(exception_target, exception_target, exception_target,
196 jsgraph()->Dead());
197 }
198 }
199
200 NodeVector values(local_zone_);
201 NodeVector effects(local_zone_);
202 NodeVector controls(local_zone_);
203 for (Node* const input : end->inputs()) {
204 switch (input->opcode()) {
205 case IrOpcode::kReturn:
206 values.push_back(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(input, 1));
207 effects.push_back(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(input));
208 controls.push_back(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(input));
209 break;
210 case IrOpcode::kDeoptimize:
211 case IrOpcode::kTerminate:
212 case IrOpcode::kThrow:
213 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), input);
214 break;
215 default:
216 UNREACHABLE();
217 }
218 }
219 DCHECK_EQ(values.size(), effects.size());
220 DCHECK_EQ(values.size(), controls.size());
221
222 // Depending on whether the inlinee produces a value, we either replace value
223 // uses with said value or kill value uses if no value can be returned.
224 if (!values.empty()) {
225 int const input_count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
226 Node* control_output = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(input_count),
227 input_count, &controls.front());
228 values.push_back(control_output);
229 effects.push_back(control_output);
230 Node* value_output = graph()->NewNode(
231 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, input_count),
232 static_cast<int>(values.size()), &values.front());
233 Node* effect_output =
234 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(input_count),
235 static_cast<int>(effects.size()), &effects.front());
236 ReplaceWithValue(call, value_output, effect_output, control_output);
237 return Changed(value_output);
238 } else {
239 ReplaceWithValue(call, jsgraph()->Dead(), jsgraph()->Dead(),
240 jsgraph()->Dead());
241 return Changed(call);
242 }
243}

245FrameState JSInliner::CreateArtificialFrameState(
246 Node* node, FrameState outer_frame_state, int parameter_count,
247 FrameStateType frame_state_type, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
248 Node* context, Node* callee) {
249 const int parameter_count_with_receiver =
250 parameter_count + JSCallOrConstructNode::kReceiverOrNewTargetInputCount;
251 const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
252 common()->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(
253 frame_state_type, parameter_count_with_receiver, 0, shared.object());
254
255 const Operator* op = common()->FrameState(
256 BytecodeOffset::None(), OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), state_info);
257 const Operator* op0 = common()->StateValues(0, SparseInputMask::Dense());
258 Node* node0 = graph()->NewNode(op0);
259
260 Node* params_node = nullptr;
261#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
262 const bool skip_params =
263 frame_state_type == FrameStateType::kWasmInlinedIntoJS;
264#else
265 const bool skip_params = false;
266#endif
267 if (skip_params) {
268 // For wasm inlined into JS the frame state doesn't need to be used for
269 // deopts. Also, due to different calling conventions, there isn't a
270 // receiver at input 1. We still need to store an undefined node here as the
271 // code requires this state values to have at least 1 entry.
272 // TODO(mliedtke): Can we clean up the FrameState handling, so that wasm
273 // inline FrameStates are closer to JS FrameStates without affecting
274 // performance?
275 const Operator* op_param =
276 common()->StateValues(1, SparseInputMask::Dense());
277 params_node = graph()->NewNode(op_param, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
278 } else {
279 NodeVector params(local_zone_);
280 params.push_back(
281 node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::ReceiverOrNewTargetIndex()));
282 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
283 params.push_back(node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(i)));
284 }
285 const Operator* op_param = common()->StateValues(
286 static_cast<int>(params.size()), SparseInputMask::Dense());
287 params_node = graph()->NewNode(op_param, static_cast<int>(params.size()),
288 &params.front());
289 }
290 if (context == nullptr) context = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
291 if (callee == nullptr) {
292 callee = node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::TargetIndex());
293 }
294 return FrameState{graph()->NewNode(op, params_node, node0, node0, context,
295 callee, outer_frame_state)};
296}

300bool NeedsImplicitReceiver(SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info) {
301 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
302 return !shared_info.construct_as_builtin() &&
303 !IsDerivedConstructor(shared_info.kind());
304}

308// Determines whether the call target of the given call {node} is statically
309// known and can be used as an inlining candidate. The {SharedFunctionInfo} of
310// the call target is provided (the exact closure might be unknown).
311OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef JSInliner::DetermineCallTarget(Node* node) {
312 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsInlineeOpcode(node->opcode()));
313 Node* target = node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::TargetIndex());
314 HeapObjectMatcher match(target);
315
316 // This reducer can handle both normal function calls as well a constructor
317 // calls whenever the target is a constant function object, as follows:
318 // - JSCall(target:constant, receiver, args..., vector)
319 // - JSConstruct(target:constant, new.target, args..., vector)
320 if (match.HasResolvedValue() && match.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
321 JSFunctionRef function = match.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
322
323 // The function might have not been called yet.
324 if (!function.feedback_vector(broker()).has_value()) {
325 return base::nullopt;
326 }
327
328 // Disallow cross native-context inlining for now. This means that all parts
329 // of the resulting code will operate on the same global object. This also
330 // prevents cross context leaks, where we could inline functions from a
331 // different context and hold on to that context (and closure) from the code
332 // object.
333 // TODO(turbofan): We might want to revisit this restriction later when we
334 // have a need for this, and we know how to model different native contexts
335 // in the same graph in a compositional way.
336 if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(
337 broker()->target_native_context())) {
338 return base::nullopt;
339 }
340
341 return function.shared(broker());
342 }
343
344 // This reducer can also handle calls where the target is statically known to
345 // be the result of a closure instantiation operation, as follows:
346 // - JSCall(JSCreateClosure[shared](context), receiver, args..., vector)
347 // - JSConstruct(JSCreateClosure[shared](context),
348 // new.target, args..., vector)
349 if (match.IsJSCreateClosure()) {
350 JSCreateClosureNode n(target);
351 FeedbackCellRef cell = n.GetFeedbackCellRefChecked(broker());
352 return cell.shared_function_info(broker());
353 } else if (match.IsCheckClosure()) {
354 FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(match.op()));
355 return cell.shared_function_info(broker());
356 }
357
358 return base::nullopt;
359}
360
361// Determines statically known information about the call target (assuming that
362// the call target is known according to {DetermineCallTarget} above). The
363// following static information is provided:
364// - context : The context (as SSA value) bound by the call target.
365// - feedback_vector : The target is guaranteed to use this feedback vector.
366FeedbackCellRef JSInliner::DetermineCallContext(Node* node,
367 Node** context_out) {
368 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsInlineeOpcode(node->opcode()));
369 Node* target = node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::TargetIndex());
370 HeapObjectMatcher match(target);
371
372 if (match.HasResolvedValue() && match.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
373 JSFunctionRef function = match.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
374 // This was already ensured by DetermineCallTarget
375 CHECK(function.feedback_vector(broker()).has_value());
376
377 // The inlinee specializes to the context from the JSFunction object.
378 *context_out =
379 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.context(broker()), broker());
380 return function.raw_feedback_cell(broker());
381 }
382
383 if (match.IsJSCreateClosure()) {
384 // Load the feedback vector of the target by looking up its vector cell at
385 // the instantiation site (we only decide to inline if it's populated).
386 JSCreateClosureNode n(target);
387 FeedbackCellRef cell = n.GetFeedbackCellRefChecked(broker());
388
389 // The inlinee uses the locally provided context at instantiation.
390 *context_out = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(match.node());
391 return cell;
392 } else if (match.IsCheckClosure()) {
393 FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(match.op()));
394
395 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
396 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
397 *context_out = effect = graph()->NewNode(
398 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext()),
399 match.node(), effect, control);
400 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
401
402 return cell;
403 }
404
405 // Must succeed.
406 UNREACHABLE();
407}

409#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
410static std::string WasmFunctionNameForTrace(wasm::NativeModule* native_module,
411 int fct_index) {
412 wasm::StringBuilder builder;
413 native_module->GetNamesProvider()->PrintFunctionName(builder, fct_index);
414 if (builder.length() == 0) return "<no name>";
415 return {builder.start(), builder.length()};
416}
417
418JSInliner::WasmInlineResult JSInliner::TryWasmInlining(
419 const JSWasmCallNode& call_node) {
420 const JSWasmCallParameters& wasm_call_params = call_node.Parameters();
421 wasm::NativeModule* native_module = wasm_call_params.native_module();
422 const int fct_index = wasm_call_params.function_index();
423 TRACE("Considering wasm function ["
424 << fct_index << "] "
425 << WasmFunctionNameForTrace(native_module, fct_index) << " of module "
426 << wasm_call_params.module() << " for inlining");
427
428 if (native_module->module() != wasm_module_) {
429 // Inlining of multiple wasm modules into the same JS function is not
430 // supported.
431 TRACE("- not inlining: another wasm module is already used for inlining");
432 return {};
433 }
434 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(call_node)) {
435 // TODO(14034): It would be useful to also support inlining of wasm
436 // functions if they are surrounded by a try block which requires further
437 // work, so that the wasm trap gets forwarded to the corresponding catch
438 // block.
439 TRACE("- not inlining: wasm inlining into try catch is not supported");
440 return {};
441 }
442
443 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = wasm_call_params.signature();
444 Graph::SubgraphScope graph_scope(graph());
445 WasmGraphBuilder builder(nullptr, zone(), jsgraph(), sig, source_positions_,
446 WasmGraphBuilder::kJSFunctionAbiMode, isolate(),
447 native_module->enabled_features());
448 SourcePosition call_pos = source_positions_->GetSourcePosition(call_node);
449 // Calculate hypothetical inlining id, so if we can't inline, we do not add
450 // the wasm function to the list of inlined functions.
451 int inlining_id = static_cast<int>(info_->inlined_functions().size());
452 bool can_inline_body =
453 builder.TryWasmInlining(fct_index, native_module, inlining_id);
454 if (can_inline_body) {
455 int actual_id =
456 info_->AddInlinedFunction(wasm_call_params.shared_fct_info().object(),
457 Handle<BytecodeArray>(), call_pos);
458 CHECK_EQ(inlining_id, actual_id);
459 }
460 return {can_inline_body, graph()->start(), graph()->end()};
461}
462
463Reduction JSInliner::ReduceJSWasmCall(Node* node) {
464 JSWasmCallNode call_node(node);
465 const JSWasmCallParameters& wasm_call_params = call_node.Parameters();
466 int fct_index = wasm_call_params.function_index();
467 wasm::NativeModule* native_module = wasm_call_params.native_module();
468 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = wasm_call_params.signature();
469
470 // Try "full" inlining of very simple wasm functions (mainly getters / setters
471 // for wasm gc objects).
472 WasmInlineResult inline_result;
473 if (inline_wasm_fct_if_supported_ && fct_index != -1 && native_module &&
474 // Disable inlining for asm.js functions because we haven't tested it
475 // and most asm.js opcodes aren't supported anyway.
476 native_module->enabled_features() != wasm::WasmFeatures::ForAsmjs()) {
477 inline_result = TryWasmInlining(call_node);
478 }
479
480 // Create the subgraph for the wrapper inlinee.
481 Node* wrapper_start_node;
482 Node* wrapper_end_node;
483 size_t subgraph_min_node_id;
484 {
485 Graph::SubgraphScope scope(graph());
486 graph()->SetEnd(nullptr);
487
488 // Create a nested frame state inside the frame state attached to the
489 // call; this will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this point will
490 // still return the result of the Wasm function call.
491 Node* continuation_frame_state =
492 CreateJSWasmCallBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
493 jsgraph(), call_node.context(), call_node.frame_state(), sig);
494
495 // All the nodes inserted by the inlined subgraph will have
496 // id >= subgraph_min_node_id. We use this later to avoid wire nodes that
497 // are not inserted by the inlinee but were already part of the graph to the
498 // surrounding exception handler, if present.
499 subgraph_min_node_id = graph()->NodeCount();
500
501 bool set_in_wasm_flag = !inline_result.can_inline_body;
502 BuildInlinedJSToWasmWrapper(
503 graph()->zone(), jsgraph(), sig,
504 native_module->module()->functions[fct_index].imported,
505 wasm_call_params.module(), isolate(), source_positions_,
506 wasm::WasmFeatures::FromFlags(), continuation_frame_state,
507 set_in_wasm_flag);
508
509 // Extract the inlinee start/end nodes.
510 wrapper_start_node = graph()->start();
511 wrapper_end_node = graph()->end();
512 }
513 StartNode start{wrapper_start_node};
514
515 Node* exception_target = nullptr;
516 NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &exception_target);
517
518 // If we are inlining into a surrounding exception handler, we collect all
519 // potentially throwing nodes within the inlinee that are not handled locally
520 // by the inlinee itself. They are later wired into the surrounding handler.
521 NodeVector uncaught_subcalls(local_zone_);
522 if (exception_target != nullptr) {
523 // Find all uncaught 'calls' in the inlinee.
524 AllNodes inlined_nodes(local_zone_, wrapper_end_node, graph());
525 for (Node* subnode : inlined_nodes.reachable) {
526 // Ignore nodes that are not part of the inlinee.
527 if (subnode->id() < subgraph_min_node_id) continue;
528
529 // Every possibly throwing node should get {IfSuccess} and {IfException}
530 // projections, unless there already is local exception handling.
531 if (subnode->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow)) continue;
532 if (!NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(subnode)) {
533 DCHECK_EQ(2, subnode->op()->ControlOutputCount());
534 uncaught_subcalls.push_back(subnode);
535 }
536 }
537 }
538
539 // Search in inlined nodes for call to inline wasm.
540 // Note: We can only inline wasm functions of a single wasm module into any
541 // given JavaScript function (due to the WasmGCLowering being dependent on
542 // module-specific type indices).
543 Node* wasm_fct_call = nullptr;
544 if (inline_result.can_inline_body) {
545 AllNodes inlined_nodes(local_zone_, wrapper_end_node, graph());
546 for (Node* subnode : inlined_nodes.reachable) {
547 // Ignore nodes that are not part of the inlinee.
548 if (subnode->id() < subgraph_min_node_id) continue;
549
550 if (subnode->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCall &&
551 CallDescriptorOf(subnode->op())->kind() ==
552 CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunction) {
553 wasm_fct_call = subnode;
554 break;
555 }
556 }
557 DCHECK(wasm_fct_call != nullptr);
558 }
559
560 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
561 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
562 Node* new_target = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
563
564 // Inline the wasm wrapper.
565 Reduction r =
566 InlineJSWasmCall(node, new_target, context, frame_state, start,
567 wrapper_end_node, exception_target, uncaught_subcalls);
568 // Inline the wrapped wasm body if supported.
569 if (inline_result.can_inline_body) {
570 InlineWasmFunction(wasm_fct_call, inline_result.body_start,
571 inline_result.body_end, call_node.frame_state(),
572 wasm_call_params.shared_fct_info(),
573 call_node.ArgumentCount(), context);
574 }
575 return r;
576}
577
578void JSInliner::InlineWasmFunction(Node* call, Node* inlinee_start,
579 Node* inlinee_end, Node* frame_state,
580 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_fct_info,
581 int argument_count, Node* context) {
582 // TODO(14034): This is very similar to what is done for wasm inlining inside
583 // another wasm function. Can we reuse some of its code?
584 // 1) Rewire function entry.
585 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(call);
586 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(call);
587
588 // Add checkpoint with artificial Framestate for inlined wasm function.
589 // Treat the call as having no arguments. The arguments are not needed for
590 // stack trace creation and it costs runtime to save them at the checkpoint.
591 argument_count = 0;
592 // We do not have a proper callee JSFunction object.
593 Node* callee = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
594 Node* frame_state_inside = CreateArtificialFrameState(
595 call, FrameState{frame_state}, argument_count,
596 FrameStateType::kWasmInlinedIntoJS, shared_fct_info, context, callee);
597 Node* check_point = graph()->NewNode(common()->Checkpoint(),
598 frame_state_inside, effect, control);
599 effect = check_point;
600
601 for (Edge edge : inlinee_start->use_edges()) {
602 Node* use = edge.from();
603 if (use == nullptr) continue;
604 switch (use->opcode()) {
605 case IrOpcode::kParameter: {
606 // Index 0 is the callee node.
607 int index = 1 + ParameterIndexOf(use->op());
608 Node* arg = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(call, index);
609 Replace(use, arg);
610 break;
611 }
612 default:
613 if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
614 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
615 } else if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
616 // Projections pointing to the inlinee start are floating
617 // control. They should point to the graph's start.
618 edge.UpdateTo(use->opcode() == IrOpcode::kProjection
619 ? graph()->start()
620 : control);
621 } else {
622 UNREACHABLE();
623 }
624 Revisit(edge.from());
625 break;
626 }
627 }
628
629 // 2) Handle all graph terminators for the callee.
630 // Special case here: There is only one call terminator.
631 DCHECK_EQ(inlinee_end->inputs().count(), 1);
632 Node* terminator = *inlinee_end->inputs().begin();
633 DCHECK_EQ(terminator->opcode(), IrOpcode::kReturn);
634 inlinee_end->Kill();
635
636 // 3) Rewire unhandled calls to the handler.
637 // This is not supported yet resulting in exceptional calls being treated
638 // as non-inlineable.
639 DCHECK(!NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(call));
640
641 // 4) Handle return values.
642 int return_values = terminator->InputCount();
643 DCHECK_GE(return_values, 3);
644 DCHECK_LE(return_values, 4);
645 // Subtract effect, control and drop count.
646 int return_count = return_values - 3;
647 Node* effect_output = terminator->InputAt(return_count + 1);
648 Node* control_output = terminator->InputAt(return_count + 2);
649 for (Edge use_edge : call->use_edges()) {
650 if (NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(use_edge)) {
651 Node* use = use_edge.from();
652 // There is at most one value edge.
653 ReplaceWithValue(use, return_count == 1 ? terminator->InputAt(1)
654 : jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
655 }
656 }
657 // All value inputs are replaced by the above loop, so it is ok to use
658 // Dead() as a dummy for value replacement.
659 ReplaceWithValue(call, jsgraph()->Dead(), effect_output, control_output);
660}
661
662#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
663
664Reduction JSInliner::ReduceJSCall(Node* node) {
665 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsInlineeOpcode(node->opcode()));
666#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
667 DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSWasmCall);
668#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
669 JSCallAccessor call(node);
670
671 // Determine the call target.
672 OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info(DetermineCallTarget(node));
673 if (!shared_info.has_value()) return NoChange();
674
675 SharedFunctionInfoRef outer_shared_info =
676 MakeRef(broker(), info_->shared_info());
677
678 SharedFunctionInfo::Inlineability inlineability =
679 shared_info->GetInlineability(broker());
680 if (inlineability != SharedFunctionInfo::kIsInlineable) {
681 // The function is no longer inlineable. The only way this can happen is if
682 // the function had its optimization disabled in the meantime, e.g. because
683 // another optimization job failed too often.
684 CHECK_EQ(inlineability, SharedFunctionInfo::kHasOptimizationDisabled);
685 TRACE("Not inlining " << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
686 << " because it had its optimization disabled.");
687 return NoChange();
688 }
689 // NOTE: Even though we bailout in the kHasOptimizationDisabled case above, we
690 // won't notice if the function's optimization is disabled after this point.
691
692 // Constructor must be constructable.
693 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct &&
694 !IsConstructable(shared_info->kind())) {
695 TRACE("Not inlining " << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
696 << " because constructor is not constructable.");
697 return NoChange();
698 }
699
700 // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
701 // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
702 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall &&
703 IsClassConstructor(shared_info->kind())) {
704 TRACE("Not inlining " << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
705 << " because callee is a class constructor.");
706 return NoChange();
707 }
708
709 // To ensure inlining always terminates, we have an upper limit on inlining
710 // the nested calls.
711 int nesting_level = 0;
712 for (Node* frame_state = call.frame_state();
713 frame_state->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFrameState;
714 frame_state = FrameState{frame_state}.outer_frame_state()) {
715 nesting_level++;
716 if (nesting_level > kMaxDepthForInlining) {
717 TRACE("Not inlining "
718 << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
719 << " because call has exceeded the maximum depth for function "
720 "inlining.");
721 return NoChange();
722 }
723 }
724
725 Node* exception_target = nullptr;
726 NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &exception_target);
727
728 // JSInliningHeuristic has already filtered candidates without a BytecodeArray
729 // based on SharedFunctionInfoRef::GetInlineability. For the inlineable ones
730 // (kIsInlineable), the broker holds a reference to the bytecode array, which
731 // prevents it from getting flushed. Therefore, the following check should
732 // always hold true.
733 CHECK(shared_info->is_compiled());
734
735 if (info_->source_positions() &&
736 !shared_info->object()->AreSourcePositionsAvailable(
737 broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate())) {
738 // This case is expected to be very rare, since we generate source
739 // positions for all functions when debugging or profiling are turned
740 // on (see Isolate::NeedsDetailedOptimizedCodeLineInfo). Source
741 // positions should only be missing here if there is a race between 1)
742 // enabling/disabling the debugger/profiler, and 2) this compile job.
743 // In that case, we simply don't inline.
744 TRACE("Not inlining " << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
745 << " because source positions are missing.");
746 return NoChange();
747 }
748
749 // Determine the target's feedback vector and its context.
750 Node* context;
751 FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell = DetermineCallContext(node, &context);
752
753 TRACE("Inlining " << *shared_info << " into " << outer_shared_info
754 << ((exception_target != nullptr) ? " (inside try-block)"
755 : ""));
756 // ----------------------------------------------------------------
757 // After this point, we've made a decision to inline this function.
758 // We shall not bailout from inlining if we got here.
759
760 BytecodeArrayRef bytecode_array = shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(broker());
761
762 // Remember that we inlined this function.
763 int inlining_id =
764 info_->AddInlinedFunction(shared_info->object(), bytecode_array.object(),
765 source_positions_->GetSourcePosition(node));
766 if (v8_flags.profile_guided_optimization &&
767 FeedbackVector::cast(feedback_cell.object()->value())
768 ->invocation_count_before_stable() >
769 v8_flags.invocation_count_for_early_optimization) {
770 info_->set_could_not_inline_all_candidates();
771 }
772
773 // Create the subgraph for the inlinee.
774 Node* start_node;
775 Node* end;
776 {
777 // Run the BytecodeGraphBuilder to create the subgraph.
778 Graph::SubgraphScope scope(graph());
779 BytecodeGraphBuilderFlags flags(
780 BytecodeGraphBuilderFlag::kSkipFirstStackAndTierupCheck);
781 if (info_->analyze_environment_liveness()) {
782 flags |= BytecodeGraphBuilderFlag::kAnalyzeEnvironmentLiveness;
783 }
784 if (info_->bailout_on_uninitialized()) {
785 flags |= BytecodeGraphBuilderFlag::kBailoutOnUninitialized;
786 }
787 {
788 CallFrequency frequency = call.frequency();
789 BuildGraphFromBytecode(broker(), zone(), *shared_info, feedback_cell,
790 BytecodeOffset::None(), jsgraph(), frequency,
791 source_positions_, node_origins_, inlining_id,
792 info_->code_kind(), flags, &info_->tick_counter());
793 }
794
795 // Extract the inlinee start/end nodes.
796 start_node = graph()->start();
797 end = graph()->end();
798 }
799 StartNode start{start_node};
800
801 // If we are inlining into a surrounding exception handler, we collect all
802 // potentially throwing nodes within the inlinee that are not handled locally
803 // by the inlinee itself. They are later wired into the surrounding handler.
804 NodeVector uncaught_subcalls(local_zone_);
805 if (exception_target != nullptr) {
806 // Find all uncaught 'calls' in the inlinee.
807 AllNodes inlined_nodes(local_zone_, end, graph());
808 for (Node* subnode : inlined_nodes.reachable) {
809 // Every possibly throwing node should get {IfSuccess} and {IfException}
810 // projections, unless there already is local exception handling.
811 if (subnode->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow)) continue;
812 if (!NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(subnode)) {
813 DCHECK_EQ(2, subnode->op()->ControlOutputCount());
814 uncaught_subcalls.push_back(subnode);
815 }
816 }
817 }
818
819 FrameState frame_state = call.frame_state();
820 Node* new_target = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
821
822 // Inline {JSConstruct} requires some additional magic.
823 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct) {
824 static_assert(JSCallOrConstructNode::kHaveIdenticalLayouts);
825 JSConstructNode n(node);
826
827 new_target = n.new_target();
828
829 // Insert nodes around the call that model the behavior required for a
830 // constructor dispatch (allocate implicit receiver and check return value).
831 // This models the behavior usually accomplished by our {JSConstructStub}.
832 // Note that the context has to be the callers context (input to call node).
833 // Also note that by splitting off the {JSCreate} piece of the constructor
834 // call, we create an observable deoptimization point after the receiver
835 // instantiation but before the invocation (i.e. inside {JSConstructStub}
836 // where execution continues at {construct_stub_create_deopt_pc_offset}).
837 Node* receiver = jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(); // Implicit receiver.
838 Node* caller_context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
839 if (NeedsImplicitReceiver(*shared_info)) {
840 Effect effect = n.effect();
841 Control control = n.control();
842 Node* frame_state_inside;
843 HeapObjectMatcher m(new_target);
844 if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
845 // If {new_target} is a JSFunction, then we cannot deopt in the
846 // NewObject call. Therefore we do not need the artificial frame state.
847 frame_state_inside = frame_state;
848 } else {
849 frame_state_inside = CreateArtificialFrameState(
850 node, frame_state, n.ArgumentCount(),
851 FrameStateType::kConstructCreateStub, *shared_info, caller_context);
852 }
853 Node* create =
854 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->Create(), call.target(), new_target,
855 caller_context, frame_state_inside, effect, control);
856 uncaught_subcalls.push_back(create); // Adds {IfSuccess} & {IfException}.
857 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, create);
858 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, create);
859 // Placeholder to hold {node}'s value dependencies while {node} is
860 // replaced.
861 Node* dummy = graph()->NewNode(common()->Dead());
862 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(node, dummy, node, node, node);
863 Node* result;
864 // Insert a check of the return value to determine whether the return
865 // value or the implicit receiver should be selected as a result of the
866 // call.
867 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), node);
868 result =
869 graph()->NewNode(common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
870 check, node, create);
871 receiver = create; // The implicit receiver.
872 ReplaceWithValue(dummy, result);
873 } else if (IsDerivedConstructor(shared_info->kind())) {
874 Node* node_success =
875 NodeProperties::FindSuccessfulControlProjection(node);
876 Node* is_receiver =
877 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), node);
878 Node* branch_is_receiver =
879 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_receiver, node_success);
880 Node* branch_is_receiver_true =
881 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch_is_receiver);
882 Node* branch_is_receiver_false =
883 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch_is_receiver);
884 branch_is_receiver_false = graph()->NewNode(
885 javascript()->CallRuntime(
886 Runtime::kThrowConstructorReturnedNonObject),
887 caller_context, NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node), node,
888 branch_is_receiver_false);
889 uncaught_subcalls.push_back(branch_is_receiver_false);
890 branch_is_receiver_false =
891 graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), branch_is_receiver_false,
892 branch_is_receiver_false);
893 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), branch_is_receiver_false);
894
895 ReplaceWithValue(node_success, node_success, node_success,
896 branch_is_receiver_true);
897 // Fix input destroyed by the above {ReplaceWithValue} call.
898 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(branch_is_receiver, node_success, 0);
899 }
900 node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), receiver);
901 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
902 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
903 frame_state = CreateArtificialFrameState(
904 node, frame_state, 0, FrameStateType::kConstructInvokeStub,
905 *shared_info, caller_context);
906 }
907
908 // Insert a JSConvertReceiver node for sloppy callees. Note that the context
909 // passed into this node has to be the callees context (loaded above).
910 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall &&
911 is_sloppy(shared_info->language_mode()) && !shared_info->native()) {
912 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
913 if (NodeProperties::CanBePrimitive(broker(), call.receiver(), effect)) {
914 CallParameters const& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
915 Node* global_proxy = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
916 broker()->target_native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()),
917 broker());
918 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
919 simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()), call.receiver(),
920 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(broker()->target_native_context(),
921 broker()),
922 global_proxy, effect, start);
923 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, receiver,
924 JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex());
925 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
926 }
927 }
928
929 // Insert inlined extra arguments if required. The callees formal parameter
930 // count have to match the number of arguments passed to the call.
931 int parameter_count =
932 shared_info->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver();
933 DCHECK_EQ(parameter_count, start.FormalParameterCountWithoutReceiver());
934 if (call.argument_count() != parameter_count) {
935 frame_state = CreateArtificialFrameState(
936 node, frame_state, call.argument_count(),
937 FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments, *shared_info);
938 }
939
940 return InlineCall(node, new_target, context, frame_state, start, end,
941 exception_target, uncaught_subcalls, call.argument_count());
942}
943
944Graph* JSInliner::graph() const { return jsgraph()->graph(); }

947 return jsgraph()->javascript();
